news.title: Gurugram: Only one access road & that too blocked, Vipul Lavanya RWA writes to DTCP
news.para: A visit to the society showed that the developer, Landmark Ltd, has built a cemented block just outside the society gate, while two others have been built a few metres away, greatly reducing the width of the 24m-wide access road.

news.title: Brokers' racket keeps building plans pending for 8-9 months: Nagpur Mayor
news.para: Tiwari stated this at a meeting organized by city MP and Union minister for road transport and highways, Nitin Gadkari. Similar complaint was raised by former mayor and MLC Pravin Datke, also corporator, at the meeting.

news.title: Nagpur: NIT not recovering premium for delay, user change from Glocal Mall builder
news.para: Goel Ganga Infrastructure and Real Estate is also operating shops despite lacking occupancy certificate (OC) and rejection of application seeking the mandatory OC a few days ago.

news.title: Delhi: 32 construction sites fined under anti-dust campaign in three days
news.para: While the minister was happy with the measures being undertaken at the construction site to handle dust pollution, he said 32 construction sites out of the 103 that were inspected in the past three days, had been fined a total of Rs 15 lakh by the Delhi government for violating dust norms.

news.title: Pune: Property registrations on the rise ahead of Dasara
news.para: Officials said they expected the numbers to increase in the coming week and said the impact of the coronavirus pandemic on the real estate sector appeared to be on the wane.

news.title: Rajasthan housing department to implement zonal development plans in major cities
news.para: As per the mandatory rules, cities having more than 1 lakh population can only be regularised after the implementation of zonal development plan. For the same, the state government has to notify zonal development plan of 28 cities.

news.title: Allottees in Noida to get extension of six months due to lockdown
news.para: The condition, officials said, is that they should have been allocated the plot by Noida Authority before July 2 last year.

news.title: Mumbai: Cash piles up at BMC as builders pay premium to cut open spaces
news.para: Developers have to pay a “premium” – as it is euphemistically described – for leaving less open space around buildings, converting industrial zones into residential or commercial zones, providing less parking area, reducing width of staircases, not providing amenity spaces, cutting the size of artificial ventilations shafts, etc.

news.title: Ultratech emerges as preferred bidder for limestone block in Madhya Pradesh
news.para: The limestone mine is among five mineral blocks that have been successfully put for sale in 2021-22, according to the mines ministry.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh creates a new urban development authority
news.para: The new entity will now comprise 10 revenue mandals and 97 villages spread over a 640-sq km area, stretching from Kurada village in Visakhapatnam district to Vakalapudi in East Godavari.

news.title: Court takes cognisance of charge sheet against Avantha Group's promoter
news.para: ​Special judge Sanjeev Aggarwal summoned the accused persons and companies on five dates from October 20 to November 30, noting that the presence of such a large number of accused persons and their counsels on a single date may not be conducive for adhering to the Covid SOPs.

news.title: Goa: Uguem locals demand closure of stone quarry site
news.para: Uguem locals, in a complaint to the Mines and Geology Department, had urged authorities to shut down quarries that are functioning without valid lease from the department.

news.title: Hyderabad: Housing societies make dash to set up EV charging infrastructure
news.para: In a bid to boost EV sales and bring down the city’s carbon footprint, the Telangana government had rolled out the Telangana Electric Vehicle and Energy Storage Policy, 2020-2030, in October last year.

news.title: Property tax arrears adds to Coimbatore civic body's financial woes
news.para: A corporation official said this was 38% of the collectable property tax and they had collected only 37% of the target amount in the comparable period last fiscal.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh HC halts housing scheme, calls for assessment by expert body
news.para: The court directed the government not to proceed with construction of houses under its ‘Navaratnalu-Pedalandiriki illu’ scheme.
